				All my siblings were on Facebook so I caved. I&#39;ve gotten back in touch with a couple of good friends from high school and college and am glad for that. I&#39;ve had many, many hours of my life sucked away playing Bejeweled Blitz and several other games to prove to the sibs I can still stomp them most of the time. Well, I can still stomp them in all the word games.  And I can keep an eye on my oldest niece and remotely embarrass the crap out of her in fromt of all her friends. What&#39;s not to like? As long as you discount half the interface, most of the privacy policy, poor search, and a few other things, it&#39;s great!<br />
